==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: oecoid
<hw>oe"coid</hw> <pr>(⟦emac⟧"koid)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>o'i^kos</grk> a house + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>The colorless porous framework, or stroma, of red blood corpuscles
from which the zooid, or hemoglobin and other substances of the
corpuscles, may be dissolved out.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oecology</ent>⟦br⟧
